            "html": "<p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Watch your stuff, don't fall for any scams and if for nothing but the louvre, get the museum pass.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">A. Seriously, don't get pickpocketed. They see you coming from a mile away. Don't set your bag down, don't show people your money, don't carry a whole ton of things in a backpack and then stop in the crowd without moving your bag to the front of your body.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">B. EVERYTHING is a scam. The girls in the park with clipboards? Scam. The dudes standing outside restaurants who take you to a different restaurant? Scam. The gypsy trying to \"return\" your ring? Scam. The person trying to give you a free friendship bracelet because you are \"american girl, very pretty?\" Scam. Just don't engage with these people. Secure your purse, ignore and walk on.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 1em; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">C. The museum pass lets you get in to the louvre without queueing in the general entrance. There will still be a line in the morning, but if you get in in the first rush of people and go directly to the mona lisa, you will see it with the least amount of people around and then be free to explore the rest of the fabulous museum until you are exhausted.</span></p> <p class=\"q-text qu-display--block\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-bottom: 0px; overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; direction: ltr; text-align: start;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; background: none;\">Also, see the orsay museum and have fun.</span></p> ",
